DATASETS AND ATTRIBUTIONS
──────────────────────────
The machine learning models included with or generated by this Software were
trained using the following publicly available datasets. These datasets are
NOT distributed with this Software. Users who wish to retrain the model must
obtain each dataset independently under its respective license.

  1. ESC-50: Dataset for Environmental Sound Classification
     Author  : Karol J. Piczak
     License : Creative Commons Attribution Non-Commercial (CC BY-NC 3.0)
     Source  : https://github.com/karoldvl/ESC-50
     Citation: Piczak, K.J. (2015). ESC: Dataset for Environmental Sound
               Classification. Proceedings of the 23rd ACM International
               Conference on Multimedia, pp. 1015–1018.

  2. RAVDESS: The Ryerson Audio-Visual Database of Emotional Speech and Song
     Authors : Livingstone SR, Russo FA
     License : Creative Commons Attribution Non-Commercial Share Alike 4.0
               International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)
     Source  : https://zenodo.org/record/1188976
     Citation: Livingstone SR, Russo FA (2018). The Ryerson Audio-Visual
               Database of Emotional Speech and Song (RAVDESS): A dynamic,
               multimodal set of facial and vocal expressions in North American
               English. PLoS ONE 13(5): e0196391.
               https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0196391

The Authors gratefully acknowledge the creators of these datasets for making
them freely available for research purposes.

PRIVACY GUARANTEE
─────────────────
The Authors commit to the core privacy principles of this Software:
  - No audio is ever recorded, stored, or transmitted.
  - All ML inference runs on-device.
  - Only a numeric threat signal and GPS coordinates leave the device.

This guarantee is a design principle. Users deploying this Software in any
modified form remain solely responsible for ensuring their deployment upholds
these privacy properties.

